data.description:
1: On April 15, the US Bitcoin ETF had a net outflow of 457 BTC, and the Ethereum ETF had a net outflow of 20,604 ETH;
2: The founder of Zcash criticized Binance CEO and was dissatisfied with Binance's consideration of delisting ZEC;
3: The White House: Trump will consider banning members of Congress (stock) from trading;
4: The White House: President Trump has not yet made a decision on raising corporate tax rates;
5: OKX announced its entry into the US market and will set up a regional headquarters in California;
6: The SEC completed a two-year review of Coinbase without modification or restatement;
7: Movement co-founder Rushi Manche denied rumors of resignation;
8: The social protocol Towns Protocol confirmed that it will issue coins this quarter, with an initial airdrop of 10%;
9: Securitize acquired MG Stover's fund management business and became the largest digital asset fund management platform;
10: The CBEX Ponzi scheme broke out in Nigeria, and the amount involved may reach tens of millions of dollars;
11: ZKsync: A control value of about The administrator account of $5 million ZK tokens is suspected to have been stolen;
12: The ZKsync attacker has transferred about 1.7 million ZK tokens across the chain, and it is suspected that the cash-out operation has begun;
13: ZKsync: The administrator accounts of three airdrop distribution contracts have been hacked, and the attacker has minted about 111 million ZK tokens;
14: JPMorgan Chase CEO: The process of "deleveraging" of US Treasury bonds may have passed;
15: The US Republican Party is reportedly considering a 40% tax rate on millionaires to offset the cost of tax cuts;
16: Trump's latest crypto project will be a real estate crypto game;
17: Market news: The EU expects the United States to maintain its tariff policy;
18: US Treasury Secretary Bessant: No one thinks that tariffs on China can continue;
19: BlackRock increased its holdings by about 431 BTC, worth $37.07 million;
20: OpenAI plans to launch a social networking platform similar to X;
21: Bitwise: Bitcoin holdings of listed companies increased in Q1 2025 16.1%;
22: Analyst: XRP spot ETF may be easier to get approval from the US SEC than other assets;
23: Standard Chartered: The stablecoin market size may increase to US$2 trillion by the end of 2028;
24: BNB Chain: Lorentz mainnet hard fork upgrade is about to be carried out;
25: Paxos will transfer more than 22.2 million PYUSD to Coinbase Institutional;
26: Ethena Labs: An agreement has been reached with German regulators not to seek MiCAR authorization in the country;
27: Sol Strategies and Pudgy Penguins cooperate to launch the Solana chain PENGU validator;
28: Tether announced a strategic investment in the self-custodial crypto wallet Fizen;
29: Greeks.live: Market participants remain cautious about potential volatility, and some traders strengthen bearish positions;
30: Greeks.live: Bitcoin may hit 9

31: Trump: Will speed up the issuance of all necessary licenses to Nvidia; 

32: Only 11% of Bitcoin companies registered in El Salvador are operating normally; 

33: Optimum completes $11 million seed round of financing, led by 1kx; 

34: CleanSpark launches institutional-level Bitcoin fund management platform and receives $200 million in credit support from Coinbase Prime; 

35: NMHI, a Nasdaq-listed company involved in Bitcoin mining, reaches a financing agreement of up to $2 million; 

36: Value Creation, a Japanese listed company, plans to purchase an additional 100 million yen worth of Bitcoin.
